aVIt was taken using the Hubble Space Telescope,
p113
aVand by pointing the telescope at what was previously a blank region of sky,
p114
aVbefore the launch of Hubble.
p115
aVAnd if you can imagine this tiny area,
p116
aVit's only one-fiftieth of the size of the full moon.
p117
aVSo, if you can imagine the full moon.
p118
aVAnd there are now 10,000 galaxies visible within that image.
